raw_data.title: Senior Consultant
raw_data.description: Work with client agencies to: (1) Align managerial, organizational, and business goals with agency’s mission. (2) Provide specialized expertise in technical, challenging areas.  (3) Determine the optimal managerial, organizational, and business intervention solutions. (4) Design and execute organizational development and transformation/change management interventions. (5) Analyze systems and design new business processes. (6) Design systems to capture and disseminate knowledge and expertise. (7) Integrate research with theory and practice by providing management consulting and coaching. (8) Design program evaluation methods that are feasible, valid, and reliable. (9) Assess the return-on-investment resulting from interventions.

raw_data.title: Program Manager
raw_data.description: Work with client agencies to: (1) Develop the project plan with activities, timelines, and deliverables. (2) Establish objective, measurable performance requirements and quality standards. (3) Establish continuous improvement systems. (4) Oversee the execution of projects to ensure that performance standards are met or exceeded. (5) Acquire, allocate, and supervise project resources. (6) Anticipate and solve potential problems. (7) Exercise full authority to act for Human Technology on all matters relating to the daily operation of the project. (8) Measure project deliverables against quality standards.

raw_data.title: Consultant I
raw_data.description: Work with client agencies to: (1) Plan a project technical approach and develop a work plan.  (2) Establish objective, measurable performance requirements and quality standards. (3) Conduct comprehensive front-end and performance needs analyses. (4) Analyze performance problem areas and identify root causes. (5) Design and develop responsive, innovative interventions including: workforce planning, organizational development, classroom-based training programs; technology-enabled learning interventions; learning aids and performance support tools, knowledge management, etc. (6) Produce clear and accurate reports and other written documents. (7) Evaluate, measure, and validate the effectiveness of the delivered interventions. (8) Ensure evaluation feedback and results are incorporated into improved solutions and continuous improvement.

raw_data.title: Consultant II
raw_data.description: Work with client agencies to: (1) Establish objective, measurable performance requirements and quality standards. (2) Conduct front-end and performance needs analyses. (3) Conduct research in support of projects. (4) Develop responsive, innovative interventions  including: workforce planning, organizational development, training, and knowledge management, etc. (5) Implement strategies and solutions for performance management, pay-for-performance, pay banding, compensation and benefits. (6) Create competency models and career plans for supporting agency talent development. (7) Design and develop systems and techniques for individual and organizational assessment. (8) Produce clear and accurate reports and other written documents. (9) Evaluate, measure, and validate the effectiveness of agency program and human capital interventions.

raw_data.title: Administrative Support
raw_data.description: Work with client agencies to: (1) Coordinate arrangements for meeting/training facilities, materials, and travel. (2) Record notes during meetings and focus groups. (3) Perform quality assurance reviews of technology-based products. (4) Use software applications to produce and edit project deliverables. (5) Edit deliverables to comply with the Government Printing Office Style Manual and agency publication standards and procedures. (6) Apply information-simplification formatting principles or other techniques to enhance the readability of the materials. (7) Proofread documents to ensure that they are free of errors.
